      "description": "Low-barrier daytime navigation and respite center for adults experiencing homelessness in Austin. Open Monday–Friday, generally 9:00 a.m.–1:00 p.m. Guests can access showers (typically 9:00 a.m.–12:00 p.m.), meals and snacks, hygiene supplies, device charging, Wi‑Fi, computer lab support, mail services, medication storage, and on‑site connections to mental health and substance use services. Staff can also help clients get on the City of Austin shelter waitlist, complete Coordinated Assessments for housing, and access limited financial assistance for move‑in costs and IDs. Lines often begin forming before opening, so arriving early is recommended.",
      "justification": "Client needs daytime-only shelter space in Austin. Sunrise Hub is a centrally coordinated day center specifically designed for unsheltered adults, offering daytime indoor space, showers, food, and navigation to city shelter and housing resources.",
      "referral_type": "external"
    },
    {
      "name": "LifeWorks Youth Resource Center (Drop‑In Day Center for Ages 16–26)",
      "addresses": [
        "835 North Pleasant Valley Rd, Austin, TX 78702"
      ],
      "phones": [
        "512-473-9125",
        "512-735-2400"
      ],
      "emails": [
        "LWinfo@lifeworksaustin.org"
      ],
      "website": "https://www.lifeworksaustin.org/housing-basic-needs/basic-needs",
      "description": "Drop‑in daytime resource center for youth and young adults roughly ages 16–26 experiencing homelessness or housing instability. Open Monday–Thursday, typically 12:00 p.m.–4:00 p.m. The center offers hot meals, snacks, showers, clothing, a safe place to rest indoors, and supportive staff who can help with housing navigation, counseling referrals, and other basic needs. All services are free and no appointment is required during walk‑in hours. LifeWorks can also connect minors (17 and under) to their 24‑hour youth emergency shelter via the emergency shelter line.",
      "justification": "For clients who are youth or young adults, this is a dedicated daytime drop‑in space in Austin that functions as a day shelter with food, rest areas, and showers.",
      "referral_type": "external"
    },
    {
      "name": "The Charlie Center – Homeless Hospitality & Navigation (Northwest Austin Day Center)",
      "addresses": [
        "12675 Research Blvd, Austin, TX 78759"
      ],
      "phones": [
        "512-922-8954"
      ],
      "emails": [
        "leah@thecharliecenter.org"
      ],
      "website": "https://www.thecharliecenter.org/need-help",
      "description": "Daytime homeless navigation and hospitality center in Northwest Austin. Currently open Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays from 10:00 a.m.–1:00 p.m. Provides a hot meal, help with IDs and vital records, access to medical and behavioral health referrals, Coordinated Assessments for housing, case management, mailing address services, and secure storage for documents and medications. Hot showers are available on Wednesdays. Designed as a safe indoor space for unsheltered adults to rest, eat, and connect with services during the day.",
      "justification": "Client requested daytime-only shelter options. The Charlie Center offers limited-hours daytime hospitality (food, showers, navigation) for adults, functioning as a part-time day shelter in Austin.",
      "referral_type": "external"
    }
  ]
}

